. S. military engagement in Iraq and Afghanistan. Can a war be just? What is the relation between the ruler and the ruled? What motivates ethnic violence? Shakespeare’s plays serve as the frame for careful explorations of perennial problems of human co-existence: the politics of honor, the ethics of diplomacy, the responsibility of non-combatants, and the tension between idealism and Realpolitik.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aLiterature and history. 0aPolitics and literature. 0aWar in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aJust War Theory.  aPacifism.  aRepresentations of War.  aShakespeare and Honour.  aShakespeare and War.  aShakespeare.1 aCurrell, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDailey, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrin, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Patrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aQuabeck, Franziska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoncini, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTronch, Jesús, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWong, Jane Yeang Chui, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311099772940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781789202632?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781789202632423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781789202632/original  a978-3-11-099772-9  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_